						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the Vēṇugōpālasvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Piṅgaḷa, Kārttīka śu. 2.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of the shrine of Hanumantasvāmi by a certain Pedda-Pāpayya, son of Narāla-Gōvindu. In characters of the 15th century A.D.</p>						

